\begin_layout Section*
Stability within Ecosystems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Although we generalized the relationship of species composition to biomass
 driven by climate above, we know that different types of ecosystems have
 different responses to climate drivers.
 These responses depend on stabilizing feedbacks within different types
 of ecosystems.
 We calculate absolute change to show which systems have the largest stabilizing
 feedbacks over the Holocene (Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:posteriors-of-change"

\end_inset

).
 Here, we see that stability of an ecosystem increases with biomass.
